# EngE-AI: Development Rules

EngE-AI is an AI-powered study assistant for engineering courses at UBC. Students ask course-related questions and receive guided responses that build critical thinking. Instructors upload materials, monitor interactions, and manage the AI knowledge base.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** Vanilla TypeScript, HTML, CSS
- **Backend:** Node.js (Express), TypeScript
- **Databases:** MongoDB (courses, users, chats, flags), Qdrant (vector search via UBC GenAI Toolkit)
- **AI:** ChatGPT API, custom RAG with document chunking and embeddings

---

## Implemented Features

### Student Features

| Feature | Description | Key Files |
|---------|-------------|-----------|
| **Chat** | RAG-powered chat with streaming responses. Uses course materials for context. Supports pin/unpin, delete, restore. | `feature/chat.ts`, `render-chat.ts`, `functions/chat-api.ts`, `ChatApp.ts` |
| **Profile** | View and update user profile, onboarding state | `profile/` |
| **Flag history** | View flags the student has submitted | `feature/student-flag-history.ts` |
| **About** | About page | `about/about.ts` |
| **Onboarding** | Student onboarding flow | `onboarding/student-onboarding.ts` |

### Instructor Features

| Feature | Description | Key Files |
|---------|-------------|-----------|
| **Documents** | Upload and manage course materials for RAG (text, PDF, DOCX). Organize by topic/week/item. | `feature/documents.ts`, `RAGService.ts`, `rag-app.ts`, `rag-routes.ts` |
| **Flags** | View, respond to, and resolve student flags (inaccurate response, harassment, inappropriate, etc.) | `feature/flags.ts`, `mongo-routes.ts` |
| **Monitor** | View chat titles for all students; download full conversations | `feature/monitor.ts`, `mongo-routes.ts` |
| **Instructor chat** | Same chat interface as students, for testing | `feature/chat.ts` |
| **Assistant prompts** | Create/edit/select initial assistant messages for new student chats | `feature/assistant-prompts.ts` |
| **System prompts** | Configure AI behavior (base prompt, learning objectives, struggle topics) | `feature/system-prompts.ts` |
| **Course information** | Edit course name, instructors, TAs, structure | `feature/course-information.ts` |
| **Onboarding** | Course setup, document setup, flag setup, monitor setup | `onboarding/course-setup.ts`, `document-setup.ts`, `flag-setup.ts`, `monitor-setup.ts` |
| **New course** | Create new course (no courseId) | `onboarding/` |

### Shared Features

| Feature | Description | Key Files |
|---------|-------------|-----------|
| **Course selection** | List courses, enter by ID or 6-char code | `course-selection.ts`, `course-entry.ts` |
| **Auth** | CWL login, logout, session | `auth-manager.ts`, `AuthService.ts`, `auth.ts`, `passport.ts` |

### Technical Features (Under the Hood)

| Feature | Description | Key Files |
|---------|-------------|-----------|
| **Memory Agent** | Analyzes chat to detect topics students struggle with. Stores per-user in MongoDB. Injects struggle words into new chat prompts. Students can dismiss "unstruggle" blocks. | `memory-agent/memory-agent.ts`, `ChatApp.ts` |
| **Artefact** | Renders Mermaid diagrams in chat responses. Detects code blocks, parses, displays in modal. | `feature/artefact.ts` |
| **RAG** | Document upload → chunking → embeddings → Qdrant. Vector search for context retrieval. | `rag-app.ts`, `RAGService.ts`, `ubc-genai-toolkit-rag` |

