## Build System & TypeScript

- **Source:** All frontend TS in `public/scripts/`. Output in `public/dist/`.
- **NEVER** edit `public/dist/*.js` — it is generated from TypeScript.
- **HTML:** `<script>` tags must point to `/dist/*.js`, not `/scripts/*.ts`.
- **Build:** Run `tsc` (or project build) to compile. Manual translation if build is unstable.

---

## Styling

- **Global:** `public/styles/style.css` — shared styles
- **Page-specific:** Only when a page has many unique styles; name after page (e.g. `dashboard.css`)
- **Order:** Link global `style.css` first, then page-specific
- **All CSS in `.css` files** — no inline styles or `<style>` blocks

### HTML Class Names & CSS Selectors

- **Class names:** Use lowercase, words separated by `-` (kebab-case). Be descriptive.
- **Avoid:** Generic names (`box`, `item`), camelCase (`myClass`), underscores (`my_class`)
- **Prefer:** `.chat-message-container`, `.flag-report-row`, `.modal-backdrop`
- **BEM-style (optional):** `.chat-message`, `.chat-message__copy-btn`, `.chat-message--pinned`
- **IDs:** Use sparingly; prefer classes for styling. If using IDs, same kebab-case.
- **Cleanup:** Remove unused classes and CSS rules. Keep selectors specific enough to avoid collisions.

**Examples:**
- ✅ `.student-flag-history`, `.assistant-prompt-card`, `#close-artefact-btn`
- ❌ `.StudentFlagHistory`, `.assistantPromptCard`, `.box`

